The paper proposes a metric for no-reference quality assessment of contrast distorted images, which involves image processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also involves the use of entropy and regression analysis, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information theory (cs.IT), respectively. Additionally, the paper uses machine learning techniques for classification, which falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG).
